sql:
SELECT soil_type
FROM soil_profiles
WHERE area_name = 'Nulato Hills Area, Alaska';

SELECT AVG(organic_matter_rv) AS average_organic_matter
FROM horizons
WHERE profile_id = 0;

SELECT COUNT(profile_id) AS profile_count
FROM soil_profiles
WHERE area_name = 'Nulato Hills Area, Alaska';

SELECT horizon_name
  FROM horizons
  WHERE profile_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Organic matter content is an important factor in determining soil fertility and overall health; 
- Soil profiles with higher organic matter content are generally more fertile and better suited for plant growth; 
- Mineral components in soil play a crucial role in providing essential nutrients to plants; 
- Higher average organic matter content typically indicates better soil quality and structure.
